ons—the main title uses overline and underline markers, while the subsections like \"コードサンプル\" and \"仕様\" use their own heading levels. So these are actually table row headers within the attributes section, not separate RST headings. The knowledge file breaks down the source's single large table into five distinct sections—covering common attributes, popup-specific attributes, button-specific attributes, and internal structure—which makes sense as a way to organize the information logically.\n\nNow I'm checking the hints across each section to make sure they're comprehensive. s1 covers button variations and common attributes, s2 handles non-popup attributes like double submission prevention, s3 focuses on icon display for popup and generic buttons, s4 addresses popup window configuration, and s5 includes the lockTarget attribute for exclusive control across confirm and delete button types.\n\nLooking at s5 more closely, lockTarget applies to a broader set of button types than what's currently captured in the hints—it covers confirm, check, update, delete, search, download, popup, and submit buttons. The hints are missing several of these button type references, which is a minor gap. Additionally, the internal structure section mentions nablarch.js but lacks references to stylesheet paths and tag locations, which should probably be included for completeness. So the tag file reference is actually describing what the button widget implements, making \"ボタンウィジェット本体\" a reasonable interpretation rather than fabrication. But I'm noticing the s5 hints are missing several button tag variants that lockTarget applies to—like button:check for 確認ボタン, button:update for 更新ボタン, and others—while the hints only list button:confirm and button:delete, which don't match the actual tag names in the source. Looking at the internal structure components like nablarch.js, base.less, and the button tag files, I notice the hints don't reference these implementation details, though that's a minor gap. Consolidating my findings, I don't see any critical omissions or fabrications in the hints themselves—the main issue is that several button tag names used in lockTarget (button:check, button:update, button:search, button:download, button:submit, button:popup) aren't included as hints in the s5 section. Let me re-examine the comment attribute to see if there are any genuine critical issues I'm missing.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":16856,"cache_read_input_tokens":18400,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":16856,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"feb84776-2b46-4f97-b3f1-63163cb6ee79","uuid":"1a34b8f6-4c2c-46e6-adff-df11d759b96c"}
